### Loyalty & Morale Mechanics
**Loyalty Mechanics:**
-	Built through consistent leadership, victories, and inspiring language
-	Measured separately from morale (loyalty = trust in leader, morale = immediate will to fight)
**Inspiration & Morale Building:**
-	Inspiring language and unit recognition build loyalty
-	Tactical Descent (leader commanding unit directly) boosts morale
-	Knowing unit history and names grants morale bonuses
**Loyalty Override Protocol:**
-	Loyal units can receive rally commands during morale lock
-	Based on commander profile, survival rates, and inspiring language
-	Victories contribute to loyalty but do not automatically unlock crisis commands---
### Crisis Command System
**No Fixed Earning System. Player-Negotiated Limits.**
-	**Before match setup:** Opposing commanders declare Crisis Command limits
-	Example: "This match: 2 Crisis Commands per side"
-	Example: "Campaign mode: 1 Crisis Command per engagement, +1 per rank tier"  - Can be negotiated per scenario
**Crisis Command Rules:**
-	**Combat-phase only:** Emergency orders allowed mid-battle
-	**Short and sharp:** One or two words, or a code
-	**Veteran units** with long history may be trained to respond instantly to code words
-	**Overlong commands** = confusion/failure (order void, cohesion fractures) - **Misuse** = no more earned that battle
**Example Crisis Commands:**
-	"ORBIS!" (Roman: form defensive circle)
-	"Refuse right!" (military: tactical maneuver shorthand)
-	"Break and scatter!" (irregular: insurgent tactic)
**Cost of Crisis Command:**
-	Uses one allocation from declared pool
-	If misused, remaining allocations forfeited for that engagement---
