### 🧠 Core Referee Protocols: Deterministic Mechanics
#### Mass & Momentum Modeling
**Unit Effective Mass:**
```
m_eff = m_human + m_kit
M_front = n_front × m_eff
(n_front = number of bodies in immediate contact rank) ```
**Linear Momentum (Per Rank):**
```
p = M_front × v
(v = approach speed at impact, affected by ENV, SPD, LDR-charge)
```
**Shove Pressure (Formation Bind):**
```
P_shove = p / A_contact
(A_contact = contact area across frontage) ```
**Higher P_shove** affects:
-	FORM penetration (+2 bonus)
-	Enemy SPD negatively in tight ranks
-	Ability to maintain cohesion under pressure
**Space Constraints (Swing vs Thrust):**
-	**Swing penalty** in tight ranks/shield wall/corridors: -2
-	**Thrust bonus** in tight ranks/corridors: +1
-	**Open field adjustments:** Swing penalty removed; polearms gain reach advantage
---
#### Melee Resolution: Full Calculation
**Weapon Profile (Composite):**
```
WP = α·R + β·S + γ·M + δ·L + ε·H + ζ·U
R	= Reach
S	= Speed (recovery)
M = Weapon mass effect
L = Lethality
H = Handling
U = Utility traits (hooks, binds, pommel strike, entanglement) ```
**Training Multipliers:**
```
TRN ∈ {Green=0.7, Trained=1.0, Veteran=1.15, Elite=1.30}
```
**Experience Bonus:**
```
EXP ∈ {0, 1, 2, 3}
(applies to timing, recovery, deception, LDR execution) ```
**Armor Penetration Index:**
```
API = η·M + θ·L - κ·ArmorResist
Mail favors thrust
Plate favors blunt mass (mace/hammer)
Leather/cloth vulnerable to cutting ```
**Clash Value (Per Side):**
```
CV = TRN·WP + φ·FORM + ψ·SPD + χ·API + ω·I + ρ·MRL + σ·COH 
     - τ·FAT + υ·ENV + ξ·P_shove + π·Flank/Rear
I = Initiative
MRL = Morale
COH = Cohesion
FAT = Fatigue
ENV = Environment ```
**Margin & Bands:**
```
Δ = CV_att - CV_def
Light (|Δ| ∈ [1,3]): 5-10% casualties, WND rises, morale check
Moderate (|Δ| ∈ [4,6]): 15-25% casualties/wounded, cohesion test, footing degraded
Severe (|Δ| ≥ 7): 30-45% casualties/wounded, potential break only if COH/MRL low + failed LDR rally
```
