## ⚔️ SECTION 8: VICTORY DOCTRINE
### Asymmetry of Victory
**Attacker's Burden:**
-	Must rout, break, or encircle the defender
-	If defender still holds cohesion, attacker has failed
-	Costs for attack (casualties, ammo, time) are high
**Defender's Law:**
-	Wins by enduring
-	If not routed, they claim victory by default
-	Can bleed attacker while preserving force
### Time as a Weapon
**There is no artificial time limit.**
-	Every day, every turn, every pause bleeds cohesion from attacker
-	Defender feeds on time; attacker is consumed by it
-	Cohesion loss per day of stalemate: -1 to -2 COH (cumulative)
### Cohesion as True Clock
**Cohesion represents:**
-	Morale
-	Fatigue- Hunger
-	Supply
-	Discipline
**When cohesion breaks, army collapses—even without a charge.**
### The Puzzle of War
-	Attacker must gamble on shock and decisive action
-	Defender must gamble on patience and endurance
-	Victory is not symmetrical—each side plays different game
